text: Vlad Țepeș is a commune in Călărași County, Muntenia, Romania. As of 2002 Vlad Țepeș has a population of 2,559. It is named after Vlad Țepeș, and its other village, Mihai Viteazu, is named after Michael the Brave. ==References== Category:Communes in Călărași County Category:Localities in Muntenia Category:Vlad the Impaler
title: Vlad Țepeș, Călărași
